htmlDescription.htmlText:
Old 1950's JT homestead recently renovated & stylishly decorated on 2.5 acres, surrounded by protected Gov't land for added space/ privacy, dotted with desert natives & views. The cabin is perfect for solo travelers, couples, friends or small families wanting to escape the hustle, reconnect and make memories. Sit by the fire and stargaze after a day at the park, pursuing the funky shops in the village or attending a music festival. Charm, serenity & adventure awaits YOU at the Desert Daze!

The space
Close enough to everything but far enough away to get the best views of the stars.
The space is all you need for a few nights or a few weeks. Fully stocked house. We even have two sleeping bags ready to go if you choose to sleep under the stars. Just put them on our two lounge chairs, find your perfect viewing spot and gaze away. Wanting a little more adventure? Take one of the many guided tours and trek across the park or rock climb while the sun is setting. You can listen to live music at one of the many venues. Love art? There is a Joshua Tree Art Walk every 2nd Saturday of the month. If you are needing an extra space/house for friends or family, there is another Airbnb, Post Modern, walking distance away.
JTNP 15 minutes
JT Village 15 minutes
JT Music festival 6 minutes
Integratron 19 minutes
Pappy and Harriets 30 minutes
Fire pit, games, views and stars. Stocked kitchen and bathroom and cozy bed.
*****Please note that you do have to drive down an unpaved road for about 2 miles.

Guest access
Guests have access to entire place

Other things to note
Please note that you will have to drive down an unpaved road for about 1.5 miles
WIFI works most of the time but on occasion when it is windy or severe weather it may not b available

html.htmlText: I live in Dana Point so I will not always be there to greet you but have local contacts that can assist if needed.  You self check in with lock box.
Superhosts are experienced, highly rated hosts who are committed to providing great stays for guests.

hostProfileDescription.htmlText: I am a mother to 5, wife to 1. I don't have a fancy job (stay at home mom). I haven't traveled the world (Mexico and Hawaii). I am not an artist (maybe in my mind). I AM excited to offer a place in the desert for a seeker to reflect, a couple to connect or re-connect and families to disconnect and make memories. I am a firm believer, especially in this day and age, that people need to put their gadgets down and listen to the silence. Put your phones away and listen to your partner or your child. Turn off the TV and play a game or go outside and see the world. I hope that is the gift you find when you visit the desert, whether in my place or someone else's.....
